Hi, I'm Daniel.

Backend developer. Systems enjoyer. Production bug survivor.

I work on healthcare software in production, mostly around Java, PL/SQL, Kafka, AWS, Docker, and event-driven systems.

A lot of my time is spent close to real systems: debugging weird bugs, reading old code, handling incidents, chasing edge cases, and making things less chaotic.

Outside of work, I build things in Go such as routing engines, backend infrastructure, devtools, APIs, and experiments with distributed systems.

I like software that is simple, observable, fast enough, and boring in production.

** Current interests

- Backend engineering
- Distributed systems
- Go
- Infrastructure
- Developer tools
- Event-driven systems
- Fintech / healthtech infrastructure
- Open source
- AI agents

Still early.
Still learning.
Still shipping.
